      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction on Dec 30 article comparing how various personal strategies for saving energy would affect global warming, oil consumption and one's pocketbook</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Business Day on Dec. 30 about energy efficiency and carbon dioxide reductions misstated the relative savings a driver could achieve by switching to a large sport utility vehicle that got an additional two miles per gallon compared with switching to a car that got two more miles per gallon. Savings in the large S.U.V. are two and a half times larger, not three and a half times.</p>
      </block>
